        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 3:56PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 354 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a band of strong
thunderstorms across the western half of Concho County, with the
leading edge just northwest of Eden. This band of storms was moving
east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail, along with
frequent lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Brownwood, Early, Bangs, Blanket, Camp Bowie, Trickham, Zephyr,
Brookesmith, and Owens.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
